
Overview of noun experiment

The noun experiment has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (59) experiment, experimentation -- (the act of conducting a controlled test or investigation)
2. (12) experiment, experimentation -- (the testing of an idea; "it was an experiment in living"; "not all experimentation is done in laboratories")
3. (7) experiment -- (a venture at something new or different; "as an experiment he decided to grow a beard")

Overview of verb experiment

The verb experiment has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (17) experiment -- (to conduct a test or investigation; "We are experimenting with the new drug in order to fight this disease")
2. experiment, try out -- (try something new, as in order to gain experience; "Students experiment sexually"; "The composer experimented with a new style")
